  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

        <h2 id="what-is" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">What Is BJJ Gym Software?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
          <strong>BJJ gym software</strong> is a management platform designed specifically for Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu academies. Unlike generic martial arts software, BJJ-specific tools understand the unique aspects of Jiu-Jitsu: the belt and stripe system, the distinction between gi and no-gi training, the competition-focused culture, and the longer timeline to black belt.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The best BJJ software handles student management, belt progression tracking, class scheduling for different training types, attendance monitoring, competition records, and billing—all using terminology and workflows familiar to BJJ practitioners. At MyDojo, we've built tools that work for pure BJJ academies as well as <a href="/mma-gym-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">MMA gyms</a> that include BJJ in their curriculum.
        </p>

        <h2 id="belt-tracking" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">BJJ Belt and Stripe Tracking</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          The BJJ belt system is unique in martial arts. The journey from white to black belt typically takes 10-15 years, with each belt representing a significant investment of time and skill development. Your software needs to track this progression accurately.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">The BJJ Belt System</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-200">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-brand-navy">Belt</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-brand-navy">Typical Time</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-brand-navy">Focus Areas</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">White Belt</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">1-2 years</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Fundamental positions, basic submissions, survival</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Blue Belt</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">2-3 years</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Technique expansion, competition introduction, game development</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Purple Belt</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">2-3 years</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Advanced techniques, teaching fundamentals, strategy refinement</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Brown Belt</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">1-2 years</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Mastery preparation, teaching advanced concepts, competition excellence</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">Black Belt</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Ongoing</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Continued learning, teaching, degrees (1st-6th dan)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          For a comprehensive breakdown of the BJJ ranking system, including stripe requirements and IBJJF minimum time rules, see our <a href="/blog/bjj-belts-order-complete-guide/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">complete guide to BJJ belts</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Stripe Tracking</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Each belt (except black) typically includes up to four stripes awarded between belt promotions. Stripes recognize progress and keep students motivated during the long journey between belts. Your software should:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-8">
          <li>Track current belt and stripe count for each student</li>
          <li>Record stripe award dates and awarding instructor</li>
          <li>Monitor attendance thresholds for stripe eligibility</li>
          <li>Alert instructors when students approach promotion criteria</li>
          <li>Generate promotion certificates and update records automatically</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="features" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Essential Features for BJJ Academies</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Gi & No-Gi Class Management</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Schedule and track attendance separately for gi and no-gi classes. Many students train both, and your software should reflect their complete training picture.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Open Mat Scheduling</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Manage open mat sessions with capacity limits, skill-level requirements, and optional check-in to track participation without formal instruction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Competition Team Management</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Identify competitors, track competition schedules, manage team registrations, and monitor competition results and rankings.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Kids Programme Support</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Handle the kids belt system (with additional belts between white and blue) separately from adult progression, including parent portal access.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Private Lesson Booking</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Allow students to book private sessions with specific instructors, with separate pricing and scheduling from regular classes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Membership Flexibility</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Support different membership types: unlimited, limited classes per week, gi-only, no-gi-only, or competition team add-ons.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Attendance Tracking for Promotion</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Many BJJ academies use attendance as one factor in promotion decisions. Quality software provides:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-8">
          <li><strong>Attendance reports:</strong> Total classes, gi vs no-gi breakdown, consistency over time</li>
          <li><strong>Promotion readiness indicators:</strong> Flag students meeting minimum attendance thresholds</li>
          <li><strong>Historical tracking:</strong> View attendance patterns at each belt level</li>
          <li><strong>QR code check-in:</strong> Fast, accurate attendance capture</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="competition" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Competition Management</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          BJJ has a strong competition culture. Many students compete regularly, and academies often maintain competition teams. Your software should support this:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Competition Features</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Tournament calendar:</strong> Track upcoming competitions (IBJJF, local tournaments, in-house)</li>
          <li><strong>Team registration:</strong> Manage group sign-ups and payment collection</li>
          <li><strong>Weight class tracking:</strong> Monitor students' competition weight categories</li>
          <li><strong>Results recording:</strong> Log match outcomes, submission types, points</li>
          <li><strong>Medal tracking:</strong> Maintain historical record of competitive achievements</li>
          <li><strong>IBJJF points:</strong> Track ranking points for serious competitors</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-brand-red p-4 my-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-brand-navy">Competition drives retention</p>
          <p>Students who compete typically train more consistently and stay enrolled longer. Supporting their competitive goals strengthens your academy community and retention rates.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="choosing" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Choosing BJJ Software</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">BJJ-Specific vs Generic</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Generic martial arts software often struggles with BJJ's unique requirements:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>Belt systems designed for karate's kyu/dan don't fit BJJ's five-belt progression</li>
          <li>Stripe tracking is often missing or poorly implemented</li>
          <li>No distinction between gi and no-gi training</li>
          <li>Competition tracking as an afterthought rather than core feature</li>
          <li>Kids programme with different belt colours not supported</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">What to Look For</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li><strong>True BJJ belt system:</strong> White through black with proper stripe tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Kids belt support:</strong> Additional belts for youth programme</li>
          <li><strong>Gi/no-gi distinction:</strong> Separate tracking for both training types</li>
          <li><strong>Competition features:</strong> Tournament tracking, results, team management</li>
          <li><strong>Open mat management:</strong> Informal session scheduling and check-in</li>
          <li><strong>Flexible memberships:</strong> Support for varied training packages</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Questions to Ask Vendors</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-8">
          <li>How does your stripe tracking work?</li>
          <li>Can I configure separate kids and adult belt systems?</li>
          <li>How do you handle gi and no-gi class tracking?</li>
          <li>What competition management features are included?</li>
          <li>Can students book private lessons online?</li>
          <li>Do you support IBJJF membership tracking?</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Related: <a href="/martial-arts-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">Martial Arts Software Overview</a> | <a href="/mma-gym-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">MMA Gym Software</a> | <a href="/blog/jiu-jitsu-belt-ranks/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">Jiu-Jitsu Belt Ranks Guide</a></p>

        <h2 id="faq" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
          {faqs.map((faq) => (
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">{faq.question}</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">{faq.answer}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="section bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-red to-red-700 text-white">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Level Up Your Academy?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl mb-8 opacity-90">Join BJJ academies worldwide using MyDojo to track belt progression, manage competitions, and grow their student base.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn bg-white text-brand-red hover:bg-gray-100 text-lg px-8 py-4">Start Free 14-Day Trial</a>
      <p class="text-sm mt-4 opacity-75">No credit card required. Setup in 10 minutes.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Content -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-8 text-center">Related Resources</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/martial-arts-software/" class="card p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Martial Arts Software</h3>
